[Student "W"]
{[showcards S:CT]

You are East. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \S5, West plays the \ST and North wins the \SK. To the second trick North plays the \CT and you must discard something. 

Play the \SJ.

You know that West has no high \S honor or he would have played it to the first trick. So North has the \S A Q left, plus all those \C tricks. You need to have East switch to a \H if possible.

West must be expecting to lead a \S back when he wins the \CQ which you hope he holds. Your \SJ discard may make him rethink. If your \Ss were any good why would you be discarding a winner when all you had to do was toss a small red card?

Hopefully West will come to the conclusion that this is Suit Preference for a \H return and will play his \HJ. Hopefully.}
[Play "W"]S5

[Event ""]
